      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(sessions): persist sender metadata in user turn transcript JSONL",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nTelegram group and channel conversations can share one OpenClaw session, but their durable user-turn transcript rows did not retain which participant sent each message. That made later transcript reads lose participant attribution even though the inbound channel context had it.\n\nFixes #90531.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\n- Resolve the effective reply route before preparing the durable user turn, then include sender identity only for group and channel routes.\n- Persist `senderId`, `senderName`, and `senderUsername` in the existing `message.__openclaw` envelope; intentionally exclude phone-number identity.\n- Preserve that metadata through write-hook replacements, active-run steering queues, and reply-run fallback paths.\n- Keep transcript redaction after metadata merging so configured sensitive-value redaction still applies.\n- Leave direct-message transcript behavior unchanged.\n\n## User Impact\n\nShared group/channel transcripts now retain participant attribution for every committed user turn, including turns queued behind an active run. Direct chats do not gain new persisted sender identity, and hook/redaction behavior remains intact.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Focused Vitest proof: 4 shards, 236 tests passed across transcript writing, hooks, active steering, reply fallback, session SDK, and E2E agent-runner coverage.\n- Type proof: core and core-test TypeScript lanes passed on Blacksmith Testbox.\n- Broad changed gate: `corepack pnpm check:changed` passed with zero warnings/errors on Testbox `tbx_01kw3jvt74gr6xt3b9f58gr4pg` ([run 28277620076](https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/actions/runs/28277620076)).\n- Real Telegram user proof: a group message was sent through an AWS Crabbox lease, the bot replied successfully, and the resulting JSONL user row contained all three sender fields. The lease and credentials were released after proof.\n- Codex autoreview: final branch review and each follow-up repair review returned no accepted/actionable findings.\n",
        "branch": "fix/90531-group-session-sender-metadata",
